Dipterocarpus turbinatus

    Authority   G.
      Family    Magnoliopsida:Dilleniidae:Malvales:Dipterocarpaceae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 5503

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION
   A tall and lofty evergreen tree reaching a height of up to 40-45 m and
   a girth of 4-5 m. The bole is up to 2/3 of the tree height and
   cylindrical.
   GROWING PERIOD
   Perennial.
   COMMON NAMES
   Gurjan, Garjan, Kherjong, Kural sal, Kuroil, Tilia gurjan, Kali gurjan,
   Shweat gurjan, Telia gurjan.
   FURTHER INF
   Scientific synonym: D. laevis. Gurjan can be found in Bangladesh,
   Myanmar and on the Andamen Islands at elevations between sea level and
   700 m. Relative humidity should be about 70% in January and up to 100%
   in June. The tree is very sensitive to fire. It is shade tolerant in
   youth. Yields may be about 40-60 m3/ha/year.

   Sources
   SOURCES (D. turbinatus Gaertn f. D. Laevis)
   Joshi H 1980 pp 375-382 [TEMP, RAIN, TEXT, PH, DEP, LIMITS, USE]
   Voortman R 1994 (pers. comm.)
   Zabala N 1990 pp 44-46 [TEMP, RAIN, DRA, LIMITS, LIG, USE]

